    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter" xml:id="d.1">
                <head type="title">King Ferdinand I to Miklós Oláh (Graz, 6 December 1552)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p xml:id="reg.p.1">1. He received Giovanni Battista Castaldo’s and King
                            Maximilian’s letter the other day in Leoben, as well as Castaldo and
                            András (Bonaventura) Báthori’s two attached letters, in which they write
                            about the office of the treasury and the inscriptio of the late Ferenc
                            Vízaknai’s possessions and property rights on Peter Haller’s behalf.
                            However, if Haller was made Treasurer, he could not be Councillor of
                            Sibiu; Haller should rather be City Judge of Sibiu, and an appointment
                            should be issued right away. He will write the answer to Castaldo and
                            Báthori, but they cannot draw up the appointment without Oláh, so they
                            are waiting for him here at the court. 2. He should not delay. He is
                            sending these letters to him so that he can prepare everything. He
                            should prepare Haller’s appointment to City Judge of Sibiu, and send it
                            to him via mail. He is also sending some letters that had been written
                            to Oláh, which he had kept back.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p xml:id="p.1">Ferdinandus etc. Reverendissime in Christo Pater, Fidelis sincere
                    nobis Dilecte!</p>
                <p xml:id="p.2">[1.] Superioribus diebus, cum adhuc essemus in <add corresp="scriba"
                        type="insert">oppido nostro</add><placeName>Leoben</placeName>, allatae
                    fuerunt nobis annexae litterae spectabilis et magnifici fidelis nobis dilecti
                        <persName>Iohannis Baptistae Castaldi</persName>,<note xml:id="note.1"
                        >Giovanni Battista Castaldo was Count of Cassano and Piadena.</note>
                    marchionis <placeName>Cassani</placeName> et comitis Platinae, nostri
                    consiliarii ac serenissimi principis domini, <persName>Maximiliani</persName>
                    regis Bohemiae et filii nostri carissimi bellici locumtenentis, cum <del
                        corresp="scriba"> quibus nobis adiuncti</del><add corresp="scriba"
                        type="corr">adiuncto</add> exemplo binarum litterarum, <del corresp="scriba"
                        >et suorum</del><add corresp="scriba" type="corr">quas ipse
                            <persName>Castaldus</persName></add> et spectabilis ac magnifici
                        <persName>Andreae de Bathor</persName><note xml:id="note.2">András
                        (Bonaventura) Báthori.</note> vaivodae nostri Transsylvaniensis <add
                        corresp="scriba" type="insert"><del corresp="scriba">quas</del>
                        coniunctim</add> super officio thesaurariatus et inscriptione bonorum et
                    iurium possessionariarum egregii quondam <persName>Francisci
                        Wyzacknay</persName><note xml:id="note.3">Ferenc Vízaknai
                        (†1551).</note><del corresp="scriba">quas coniunctim</del> pro egregio
                    fideli nobis dilecto <persName>Petro Haller ab Hallerstain</persName><note
                        xml:id="note.4">Peter Haller von Hallerstein (1490?–1569) was President of
                        the Council in Sibiu, and Treasurer of King Ferdinand I in Transylvania
                        between 1552 and 1553, see <hi rend="smallcap">Oborni</hi> 2002, 18 et
                        passim; <hi rend="smallcap">Gündisch</hi> 1947; and <hi rend="smallcap"
                            >Gündisch</hi> 1944.</note> consiliario nostro expediverunt, petiitque
                    dictus <persName>Castaldus</persName> a nobis perhumillime, quod easdem litteras
                    pro nostra in eundem <persName>Hallerum</persName> clementia gratiose confirmare
                    dignaremur, prout Devotio Tua ex eisdem litteris suis cognoscere poterit.<note
                        xml:id="note.5">See <hi rend="smallcap">Szabó</hi> 2008, 14.</note> Deinde
                    vero <add corresp="scriba" type="insert">in aliis litteris ad nos datis</add>
                    ostendit nobis fideliter iam dictum <persName>Hallerum</persName>, cum creatus
                    sit thesaurarius, magistrum civium <del corresp="scriba">Cibinii</del> civitatis
                    nostrae Cibiniensis<note xml:id="note.6">Sibiu.</note> esse non posse, quin
                    etiam si esse posset, tamen in fine praesentis mensis alium magistrum civium
                    eligendum fore, eoque propter iudicat ex re nostra fore, quod iudex, quem nos
                    creare debemus, nunc omnibus in rebus magistro civium <choice>
                        <orig>assist<gap extent="unknown" reason="damage" unit="word"/></orig>
                        <supplied>assist<corr>at</corr></supplied>
                    </choice> et quod ipse <persName>Hallerus</persName> iudex Cibiniensis eligatur
                    atque constituatur, et quod litterae desuper expediendae confestim istuc
                    mittantur. Super his itaque iam dicto <persName>bellico locumtenenti
                        nostro</persName><note xml:id="note.7">Giovanni Battista Castaldo.</note>
                    respondimus, tum praedictarum litterarum ab ipso et praefato vaivoda nostro <del
                        corresp="scriba">ex emandarum</del><add corresp="scriba" type="insert">super
                        officio thesaurariatus et inscriptione bonorum quondam <persName>Francisci
                            Wizacknay</persName> emanatorum confirmationem</add> tum iudicis
                    Cibiniensis institutionem per Devotionem Tuam, tamquam nostrum per <milestone
                        unit="pb"/>Hungaricam cancellariam expedire debere, ideoque id ad praesens
                    Devotione scilicet Tua ab aula nostra regia adhuc absente fieri non posse,
                    quamprimum autem reditura esset, sicuti brevi et in foras exspectaretur, tunc
                    nos operam daturos, ut expeditio statim <add corresp="scriba" type="insert"
                        >quemadmodum necessitas postulet</add> non mittatur. </p>
                <p xml:id="p.3">[2.] Quandoquidem igitur Devotio Tua ipsamet considerare potest
                    nostra plurimi referre, ne istiusmodi expeditioni longior mora interponatur.
                        <add corresp="scriba" type="insert">Nos autem de eiusdem Devotionis Tuae
                        actu nihil penitus audiamus</add>, visum est nobis Devotioni Tuae
                    supradictas litteras cum exemplis eorum, quae sunt confirmanda transmittere
                    eidem harum serie clementes iniungentes, quod non solum petitam confirmationem
                    super officio thesaurariatus atque inscriptione praenominatorum bonorum et
                    iurium possessionariorum a quondam <persName>Francisco Wyzacknay</persName><add
                        corresp="scriba" type="insert">relictorum ac per defectum seminis ad nos
                        devolutorum</add>, sed etiam necessarias et opportunas litteras <del
                        corresp="scriba">super in</del> de eligendo constituendoque suprafato
                        <persName>Petro Haller</persName> in iudicem Cibiniensem citra omnem moram
                    vel dilationem expediat <add corresp="scriba" type="insert">et ad nos per
                        postham transmittat,</add> prout <add corresp="scriba" type="insert"
                        >Devotionem Tuam</add> pro sua erga nos fide ac in pertractandis negotiis
                    nostris diligentia et promptitudine facturam esse non ambigimus. Deinde <del
                        corresp="scriba">postquam</del> transmittimus <del corresp="scriba"
                        >tibi</del><add corresp="scriba" type="corr">eidem</add> cum praesentibus
                    etiam <del corresp="scriba">litteras</del> inclusas <add corresp="scriba"
                        type="insert">litteras</add> ad Devotionem Tuam datas, quas hactenus penes
                    manus nostras retinuimus <del corresp="scriba">quia</del><add corresp="scriba"
                        type="insert">non existimantes opus esse illas Devotioni Tuae mittere
                        cum</add> eandem de die in diem ipsimet <del corresp="scriba"
                        >exspectavimus</del><add corresp="scriba" type="corr">exspectaremus</add>.
                        <add corresp="scriba" type="insert">Id quod clementer Devotioni Tuae
                        significare voluimus.</add></p>
                <p xml:id="p.4">Datum <placeName>Gratz</placeName> 6. Decembris 1552.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.5"><hi rend="italic">Probably on the outer side:</hi> Cancellario
                    Hungarico.</p>
            </div>
